MELBOURNE Feb 6 World champion swimmer Rosie Bernal and Olympic champion Kim Kang-ho will return to London next month after this month's Tokyo Olympics, the IOC said on Thursday.
Bernal, who has twice won a gold medal at the Olympics, will compete in the 200m butterfly later in the month in a competition that will see her second in the two-woman field.
The defending Olympic champion will be joined by Kim, who won two gold medals in the 200m butterfly at Rio in 2016.
The 38-year-old Kim, who has won three of her four Olympic medals in swimming at the previous two Olympics, has not been selected for the women's 400m butterfly.
"Rosie and Kim will join the 100m butterfly later in the month," the IOC said.
